elementLabel.imageGalleryPopupInfoContent:
For anonymous users: The list is maintained for current session of design studio only.

For registered users after login: It maintains the list of all images uploaded by user in several logged-in sessions. User can also attach a high resolution vector source file in allowed formats CDR/PSD/AI/PDF/EPS along with the raster image by clicking on 'Upload HD' button. You can see a right symbol with 'Upload image' button to indicate images who already have the high resolution image uploaded, which can be further replaced is needed. The high resolution source file is sent to the admin once an order is placed for reference.

PLEASE LOG-IN TO MAINTAIN YOUR IMAGE GALLERY AND ATTACH HIGH RESOLUTION SOURCE FILES WITH UPLOADED IMAGES.
elementLabel.imageQualityInfoContent: The image quality indicator lets you know if the image you have loaded has the right resolution for printing. If your image quality is poor we recommend that you upload a new image with higher resolution. Our graphics team checks every image submitted for resolution and quality requirements

VDP.importInstruct1: To import the VDP data first download the sample CSV file by clicking on the button labeled 'Download Sample CSV'.
VDP.importInstruct2: Fill the appropriate data in sample CSV file and click on 'Choose File' button to upload it. If you have an image as a variable field then please upload zip file contains the image (jpg, jpeg, png) )which names must match with image names in CSV file you are going to upload.
VDP.importInstruct3: Once you upload required files(CSV and/or zip) then click on 'Import Data'' button.
VDP.importInstruct4: * importing data will erase your existing data.
